---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from '../../../components/layout/Container.astro';
import Prose from '../../../components/layout/Prose.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <Container>
    <h1>Typography</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>UI scale (forms & dashboards)</h2>
      <p>UI typography demonstrates hierarchy used in application UI. Sizes and weights are token-driven.</p>

      <h1>Heading level 1</h1>
      <h2>Heading level 2</h2>
      <h3>Heading level 3</h3>
      <h4>Heading level 4</h4>
      <p>Regular paragraph text demonstrating body copy. Inline <code>code</code>, <strong>strong</strong>, and <em>emphasis</em> work as expected.</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Unordered list item one</li>
        <li>Unordered list item two</li>
      </ul>

      <ol>
        <li>Ordered list item one</li>
        <li>Ordered list item two</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section style="margin-top:20px;">
      <h2>Prose example (article)</h2>
      <Prose>
        <h1>The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog</h1>
        <p>This prose wrapper demonstrates typography rhythm for long-form content. It should style headings, lists, code blocks, blockquotes, and images in a readable, pleasant rhythm.</p>

        <h2>Subheading example</h2>
        <p>Inline example with <code>inline code</code> and a <a href="#">sample link</a>. Code blocks should be preserved and rendered with a monospace font.</p>

        <pre><code>// Example code block
function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}`;
}
</code></pre>

        <blockquote>
          <p>Design systems are about predictable, token-driven decisions that scale.</p>
        </blockquote>

        <p>Final paragraph to show trailing margin and spacing.</p>
      </Prose>
    </section>

  </Container>
</Layout>
